java.lang.Object

      java.util.AbstractSet<E>

Type Parameters:
E - the type of enum being stored in this set.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Streamable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Set<E>
public class StreamableEnumSet<E extends java.lang.Enum<E>>
extends java.util.AbstractSet<E>
implements java.lang.Cloneable, Streamable

An EnumSet equivalent (not a subclass, because EnumSet's implementation is private) that can be streamed.

See Also:
Streamable
